    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's just it... i don't feel like there's any strength left to find. the fog isn't just outside of me, it's inside too. everything feels so final. when i look over the edge of this canyon, it doesn't feel scary anymore. it just looks... quiet. like the only way to actually stop the weight of the walk is to just stop walking. it feels more like a conclusion than a gateway.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
